Cell[TextData[{
 "\tThe atom experiences a rapidly fluctuating electric field ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"\[DoubleStruckCapitalE]", "(", "t", ")"}], TraditionalForm]]],
 ", so the Hamiltonian is ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"H", "=", 
    RowBox[{
     SubscriptBox["H", "a"], "-", 
     RowBox[{"d", "\[CenterDot]", 
      RowBox[{"\[DoubleStruckCapitalE]", "(", "t", ")"}], " "}]}]}], 
   TraditionalForm]]],
 " also rapidly fluctuates.  The electric field causes the atom to be \
infrequently put into the excited state, with probability ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SuperscriptBox["\[ExponentialE]", 
    FractionBox[
     RowBox[{"-", 
      SubscriptBox["E", "m"]}], "kT"]], TraditionalForm]]],
 ".  However, Einstein realized that even in the absence of the black-body \
radiation (",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"i", ".", "e", ".", " ", "T"}], "=", "0"}], ")"}], 
   TraditionalForm]]],
 " the atom in the excited state would spontaneously radiate and return to \
the ground state.  Thus, at ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"T", "=", "0"}], TraditionalForm]]],
 " we expect the excited-state amplitude of an initially excited atom to obey \
",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"c", "(", "t", ")"}], "=", 
    SuperscriptBox["\[ExponentialE]", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"-", "\[Gamma]"}], " ", 
      RowBox[{"t", "/", "2"}]}]]}], TraditionalForm]]],
 ", where the excited state lifetime is ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"1", "/", "\[Gamma]"}], TraditionalForm]]],
 ".  We will use a quantum mechanical version of Einstein\[CloseCurlyQuote]s \
thermal equilibrium argument to deduce the value of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["\[Gamma]", TraditionalForm]]],
 ", without resort to quantum electrodynamics.  For convenience we will \
assume our excited state is a p-state, with ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"m", "=", "0"}], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->"TraditionalForm"],
 ", and the ground state is an s-state.  Only ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["E", "z"], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->"TraditionalForm"],
 " fluctuations of the black-body electric field cause excitation of this \
state."
}], "Text",
